    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-22T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-22T21:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/922: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-23T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 23, 1940—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 23—8:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. I am now informed that permits for re-exportation to Rangoon have been
                    revoked by order of the Government General. This appears to be a direct
                    consequence of the opening of the Burma Road <pb facs="0199" n="191"
                        xml:id="pg_191"/> and of Japanese pressure to prevent in so far as possible
                    the transfer to Rangoon of supplies for the Chinese Government. It is remarked
                    that this action as well as the action taken yesterday against the cargo of the
                    United States Far Eastern Trading Corporation closely followed the arrival of
                    the Japanese Economic Mission at Hanoi.</p>
                <p>Sent to Cavite for repetition to the Department, Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong,
                    Shanghai, Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
